[[Category:pages from wikipedia]][[en:Watatsumi Shrine (disambiguation)]][[Category:pages from wikipedia]]

The main shrine of Watatsumi is [[Shikaumi Shrines]] the ancestral shrine of the [[Azumi people]]
'''Kaijin Shrine''' (海神社, also read as Amajinja, Kaijinja, or Watatsumijinja) refers to various [[Shrine|Shinto shrines]]:
* [[Watatsumi Shrine_(Kobe)|Watatsumi Shrines]] - Located in {{ill|Tarumi-ku, Kobe|ja|垂水区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, [[Kobe]], [[Hyōgo Prefecture]]. It is a {{ill|Myōjin Taisha|ja|名神大社|lt=Shikinaisha Myōjin Taisha|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and a former {{ill|Kanpeichūsha|ja|官幣中社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Kaijin Shrine (Toyooka)|ja|海神社 (豊岡市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Located in [[Toyooka, Hyōgo|Toyooka City]], Hyōgo Prefecture. It is a Shikinaisha Myōjin Taisha and a former {{ill|Village Shrine|ja|村社|lt=Sonsha|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Kaijin Shrine (Kinokawa)|ja|海神社 (紀の川市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Located in {{ill|Kinokawa, Wakayama|ja|紀の川市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, [[Wakayama Prefecture]]. It is a former {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|ja|県社|lt=Kensha|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Kaijin Shrine (Nishinoshima)|ja|海神社 (西ノ島町)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Located in {{ill|Nishinoshima, Shimane|ja|西ノ島町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, [[Oki District]], [[Shimane Prefecture]]. It is a Shikinaisha Shōsha (minor shrine) and a former Village Shrine. * {{ill|Kaijin Shrine (Iki)|ja|海神社 (壱岐市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Located in [[Iki, Nagasaki|Iki City]], [[Nagasaki Prefecture]]. It is a Shikinaisha Taisha and a former Village Shrine.
Watatsumi Shrine can refer to the following
* [[Watatsumi Shrine_(Kobe)|Watatsumi Shrines]] * [[Watazumi Shrines]] sometimes read as Watatsumi Shrine * [[Kaijin Shrines]] sometimes read as Watatsumi Shrine * Another shrine to [[Watatsumi]]
== Other shrines ==
* {{ill|Kaido Shrine|ja|海童神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - known for its whalebone torii, Located in {{ill|Kawasoemachi|ja|川副町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, [[Saga District, Saga|Saga District]], [[Saga Prefecture]]. Former Gōsha.
== Related Articles == There are also shrines with similar names, such as '''Kaijin Shrine''' and '''Watatsumi Shrine''' (綿津見神社, Watatsumijinja). * * {{ill|Kaizumi Shrine|ja|海積神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Located in {{ill|Okazaki, Aichi|ja|岡崎市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, [[Aichi Prefecture]]. Former Village Shrine. * {{ill|Kaitomi Shrine|ja|海都見神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Located in {{ill|Yusuhara, Kōchi|ja|檮原町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, [[Takaoka District, Kōchi|Takaoka District]], [[Kōchi Prefecture]]. Former Gōsha (district shrine). *
